<HEADLINE> Turkish PM Designate to Submit Cabinet List Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Prime Minister designate
Bulent Ecevit said here Thursday that he hopes to submit the
cabinet list to President Suleyman Demirel Friday.
</P>
<P>
Ecevit, leader of the Democratic Left Party (DSP), made the
remarks at the presidential palace after he was re-assigned by
Demirel to form the 56th government.
</P>
<P>
He said the new cabinet will include ministers from the
Motherland Party (ANAP) led by ousted Prime Minister Mesut Yilmaz
and True Path Party (DYP) led by Tansu Ciller.
</P>
<P>
Independent lawmaker and Industry and Trade Minister Yalim
Erez returned his mandate for the government formation to Demirel
Wednesday two days after Ciller provided a sudden support for a
proposal for the minority government led by Ecevit.
</P>
<P>
Ecevit believed that he will not meet difficulties in getting a
vote of confidence from the parliament.
</P>
<P>
On December 21, Ecevit returned his mandate for the government
formation to Demirel as he failed to get enough support in the
parliament.
</P>
<P>
Ecevit pointed out that the would-be government will stay in
power for a short period of three months as the general elections
are expected to be held on April 18. 
</P>
</TEXT>
