<HEADLINE> China Provides Grant to Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
NAIROBI, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan and Kenyan Finance Minister Simeon Nyachae Thursday signed
exchange of letters for the Chinese government to provide a grant of about
0.6 million U.S.Dollars to the eastern African country.
</P>
<P>
The grant, worth about 35 million Shillings (0.6 million U.S.
Dollars), " will be used to finance projects to be agreed upon between the
two governments," Nyachae told reporters at the signing ceremony.
</P>
<P>
 He expressed the appreciation for China's development assistance
to Kenya in the fields such as roads, health, water, sports and
manpower since the two countries set up diplomatic relations 35 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Kenya also expects to benefit from China's great achievements made in

technology and industrialization and the immense trading opportunities
offered by China's large market, said Nyachae, urging Chinese enterprises
to increase investment in Kenya.
</P>
<P>
Tang said the donation is "another achievement" in Sino-Kenyan
cooperation on trade.
</P>
<P>
He called for more joint efforts to explore new ways and new forms
to deepen the two countries' economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Tang started his visit to Kenya Wednesday and is scheduled to fly
to Uganda Friday.
</P>
<P>
Kenya is the second stop of his 12-day African tour which include
Egypt, Tanzania and Zambia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
