<HEADLINE> Kenyan President Meets Chinese Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
NAIROBI, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi
Thursday met the visiting Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan at the
Nakuru State House.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, President Moi said Kenya and China have
maintained
good cooperation relations since the independence of his country, adding
that the mutual visits to each other country by heads of the two
governments have further enhanced friendship.
</P>
<P>
 Moi noted that China has provided Kenya with a lot of assistance in
the
 fields of sports, health and road-building.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that more Chinese enterprises would come
to invest in Kenya, expand trade and cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Moi said that the current international situation changes rapidly and
so does the situation in Africa.
</P>
<P>
It is of great importance to Africa that China as a big country stands
side by side with the developing countries, he added.
</P>
<P>
At the turn of the century, Moi said, Kenya and China should have
frequent discussions and dialogs so as to meet the changing situation in
the world.
</P>
<P>
Tang expressed his admiration to the positive contributions made by
President Moi in promoting the Sino-Kenyan and Sino-African relationship.
</P>
<P>
Tang said China is willing to discuss with Kenya for exploring new
ways and fields in strengthening bilateral economic and trade cooperation
under new circumstances for the benefits of the people of the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
 China hopes, through joint efforts with African countries, to develop
the Sino-African relationship featured by long-term stability, friendly and
true cooperation, and common development, he said.
</P>
<P>
 During his stay in Kenya, Tang also met with Kenyan Foreign Minister
Bonaya Godana, Finance Minister Simeon Nyachae and Speaker Francis ole
Kaparo.
</P>
<P>
Tang arrived in Nairobi Wednesday and will leave for Uganda Friday.
</P>
</TEXT>
