<HEADLINE> Airbus Expects China to Buy 1,381 Planes by 2017 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 7 (Xinhua) -- The European aeronautics
consortium Airbus Industrie said Thursday that it expects China to
buy 1,381 aircraft worth 112 billion euros (130 U.S. dollars) by
the year 2017.
</P>
<P>
Airbus said that China needs to replace during this period 288
aging passenger aircraft and buy 1,093 new aircraft to meet the
increasing demand of air travels at home. 
</P>
