<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Earmarks $360m for Construction of Educational Faciliti es </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 7 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Education of
Ethiopia said Thursday that it has earmarked over 360 million U.S.
Dollars for the construction and up-grade of the country's educational
institutions this year.
</P>
<P>
Shimels Letike, public relations head of the Ministry told the press
here that more than 253 million U.S. Dollars is allocated by regional
governments and the balance by the federal government.
</P>
<P>
Shimels said 494 primary and 19 secondary schools will be constructed
in various parts of the country while 332 pre-elementary schools will be up-
graded.
</P>
<P>
 He said 203 elementary and 16 secondary schools will be repaired and
114 additional class-rooms will be constructed.
</P>
<P>
He added that some 13 adults training centers are going to be
constructed in various parts of the country while nine existing ones will
also be maintained.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia is currently implementing a five-year (1997-2001) educational
program which plans to raise primary school enrollment from 3.1 million to
7 million, thus achieving an average gross enrollment ratio of 50 percent
for primary education in the country.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank and the African Development Bank (ADB) granted recently
over 135 million U.S. Dollars in loans to Ethiopia for the implementation
of its five year (1997-2001) educational program.
</P>
<P>
The five-year educational program is the first phase of a 20-year
development program designed to achieve universal primary education by the
year 2016.  
</P>
</TEXT>
