<HEADLINE> Israeli Forces Raze Lebanese Civilians' Houses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Israeli forces Thursday razed 15
houses belonging to Lebanese civilians in a south Lebanon village
where Lebanese guerrillas had wounded an Isareli soldier two days
ago.
</P>
<P>
At dawn in the day, a patrol of 30 Israeli soldiers
accompanied by 30 bulldozers came to Arnoun village, just
outside the Israelis-carved security zone in south Lebanon, and
then they destroyed the 15 houses.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, an Israeli soldier was seriously wounded by a
roadside bomb near Arnoun, which was detonated by guerrillas
of the Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah guerrillas have long been staging attacks on Israeli
troops's posts through Arnoun which has been largely depopulated
by the conflicts.
</P>
<P>
Israel carved out a self-declared security zone in south
Lebanon in 1985 with a claimed aim of protecting its north from
Lebanese guerrillas cross-border attacks.
</P>
<P>
Since then, Lebanon's resistance movements spearheaded by
Hezbollah has been fighting to oust Israeli occupying forces
out of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
