<HEADLINE> New Zealand Prime Minister to Visit Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Prime Minister Jean
Chretien Thursday announced that New Zealand Prime Minister Jenny
Shipley will pay an official visit to Canada on January 12-13.
</P>
<P>
"In 1999, we will celebrate the 60th anniversary of our
diplomatic relations with new Zealand. It is a pleasure to host
Prime Minister Shipley here at this auspicious time," said the
prime minister in a release.
</P>
<P>
"Over the years, the ties between our two nations have expanded
well beyond the Commonwealth, to include the Asia Pacific Economic
Cooperation forum, the Association of Southeast Asian Nations
regional forum and the United Nations," added Chretien.
</P>
<P>
On January 13, Prime Minister Shipley will hold meetings in
Ottawa with Prime Minister Chretien, Minister of Foreign Affairs
Lloyd Axworthy and Minister for International Trade Sergio Marchi.
</P>
<P>
This is the first New Zealand leader to pay an official
bilateral visit to Canada since 1987. 
</P>
</TEXT>
