<HEADLINE> Syrian President Nominated for New Term in Office </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Syrian incumbent President Hafez
Assad has been nominated for a fifth seven-year term in office, a
statement faxed to Xinhua said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The decision was announced Thursday by Assistant Secretary
General of the ruling Arab Socialist Baathist Party (ASBP)
Sulaiman Kaddah.
</P>
<P>
Kaddah said the leadership of the ASBP met Wednesday and
unanimously renominated Assad as the next president, whose current
tenure will expire on March 12, 1999.
</P>
<P>
Kaddah said the nomination has been submitted Thursday morning
to Speaker of People's Council (parliament) Abdel Kader Kaddura
and if the parliament approved the nomination, a referendum over
it will follow according to the constitution.
</P>
<P>
Kaddah also said the grant of another term to Assad is in line
with the people's will and aspirations, the national interests and
the requirement of the historic stage undergone by the Arab nation.
</P>
<P>
Assad has been holding the presidency since March, 1971. 
</P>
</TEXT>
