<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Police Incinerate Over 9 Kilograms of Drug </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian police said Thursday that
it incinerated over nine kilograms of harmful drugs at Sebeta, on the
outskirts of the capital Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The harmful drugs control division of the Ethiopian police said that the
harmful substances include heroin, cocaine and cannabis.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency quoted the police as saying that they have
detained 12 individuals of different nationalities in connection with drug
trafficking, two of whom are women.
</P>
<P>
The police also said the Addis Ababa High Court has sentenced the
criminals to up to three years of imprisonment and a fine of about 2,000
Birr (about 267 U.S. Dollars).
</P>
<P>
The convicts include traffickers from Nigeria, Ghana, Benin, Tanzania,
the Gambia and Ethiopia, according to the police. 
</P>
</TEXT>
