<DOCNO> XIE19990108.0034 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Set Up Regional Liaison Offices to Publicize Policie s </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, January 7 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzanian government intends
to set up liaison offices in various regions so as to make government
information easily known to the common people.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening ceremony of the Liaison Officers' Workshop in
Dar es Salaam Thursday, Permanent Secretary in the Prime Minister's Office,
Ben Moses, said that the public is entitled to get information from the
government.
</P>
<P>
Moses said experiences show that the recently adopted policies such as
those on land, health and children have not been understood by the public
because deliberate efforts have not been made to publicize them.
</P>
<P>
He said that ministries and regional commissioners will be able to
inform people about the success and problems of the government easily
through liaison officers and media organizations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
