<HEADLINE> FIFA Lifts Ban on Cameroon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On Monday Cameroon's clubs and national team were banned from
international soccer following the sports minister's failure to
cooperate with FIFA in moves to end chaos blighting the game in
the central African country.
</P>
<P>
But prime Prime Minister Peter Musonge Mafany contacted
Zurich-based FIFA this week to say the actions of the minister,
Joseph Owona, did not reflect the position of the government
which fully supported FIFA's plans.
</P>
<P>
FIFA responded by lifting the suspension. 
</P>
</TEXT>
