<DOCNO> XIE19990108.0048 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Regional Operations by Overseas Companies in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong recorded a slight
decrease in the number of regional representation by overseas
companies in 1998, according to a government survey released here
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Conducted by the Industry Department, the survey shows that
there were a total of 2,449 regional operations in Hong Kong in
1998, including 819 regional headquarters and 1,630 regional
offices.
</P>
<P>
The figure was an overall drop of 2.6 percent from the
previous year, said Director-General of Industry Francis Ho here
Friday at a press conference. The decrease was due to a 9.3
percent net fall in the number of regional headquarters, from 903
to 819.
</P>
<P>
Ho explained that overseas companies downgraded their presence
because of "high operating cost in Hong Kong" and "reducing
business prospects in the region following the Asian financial
turmoil".
</P>
<P>
The official noted that 65 new regional headquarters were
established in 1998, and 95 percent of overseas companies
responded that they would continue to operate in Hong Kong.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
