<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-08 15:17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Traffic Deaths Surges in Cyprus in Festive Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Five times as many people died
in road accidents over the festive season in 1998 compared to the
same period in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Ten people died and 39 were seriously injured from December 27,
1998 to January 7, 1999 in traffic accidents, and 95 others
suffered light injuries, according to statistics issued by Cyprus'
Ministry of Justice.
</P>
<P>
There were more than 3,000 separate cases of speeding, of which
2,028 people were given breath tests and 30 people were
subsequently charged with drink-driving.
</P>
<P>
Two people were killed on the roads over Christmas period in
the previous year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
