<HEADLINE> Relief Materials Reach Quake Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Eighteen truckloads of relief
supplies donated by international humanitarian organizations
reached earthquake victims in southwest China's Yunnan Province
earlier today.
</P>
<P>
The supplies valued at 1.24 million yuan included 80 tons of
grain, 2,000 pairs of cotton trousers, 4,200 quilts and 300
tents. The donations came from the International Federation of
the Red Cross and Red crescent, the Red Cross of Canada and the
European Union's Humanitarian Aid Office.
</P>
<P>
Some 300,000 people in Ninglang County, Yunnan Province, have
witnessed in five quakes measuring above five degrees on the
Richter scale since October last year.
</P>
<P>
Today's shipment was the first received from international
humanitarian organizations. 
