<HEADLINE> Four Robbers Shot Dead in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Four robbers were shot dead
while an accomplice and a bystander were injured in a shootout
with police here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred in Taman Bukit Maluri, Kepong, here when
five men tried to escape after robbing a Bank Simpanan Nasional
(BSN) branch and run into the policemen who were on crime
prevention patrol, the Malaysian national news agency Bernama
reported.
</P>
<P>
Four of them were shot dead on the spot another man, believed
to be a member of the gang, was injured on the thigh and has been
detained, Bernama quoted Kuala Lumpur police chief Kamarudin Ali
as saying.
</P>
<P>
A member of the public was injured on the left shoulder in the
shootout, but whose shot injured him has yet to be determined, the
police officer said, adding the injured man was warded in the
Kuala Lumpur Hospital in stable condition.
</P>
<P>
Police recovered four pieces of firearms, several car keys and
a black bag containing 33,662.75 ringgit (8,858 U.S. dollars)
believed to have been taken from the bank from the robbers, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The robbers were believed to have been involved in at least
eight criminal cases in the capital city of Kuala Lumpur and the
adjacent Selangor state, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
