<HEADLINE> Universities Launch EMBA Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 8 (Xinhua) -- People's University of China
and the State University of New York (SUNY) in Buffalo officially
launched a joint Executive Master Of Business Administration
(EMBA) program today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The first EMBA program on the Chinese mainland was approved by
the Ministry of Education.
</P>
<P>
People's University, one of China's most prestigious
institutes of higher education, was the first Chinese university
to establish an MBA program. SUNY, the first foreign university
joining Chinese universities in establishing business management
programs, joined the Dalian Institute of Science and Engineering
in launching an MBA training program in 1984.
</P>
<P>
Most of the 51 students in the new program are senior managers
for overseas-funded enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The two-year program will be conducted in English and both
universities will supply professors. Graduates will receive
degrees from SUNY.  
</P>
