<HEADLINE> Bus Between India, Pakistan Begins Dry Run </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The final dry run for the bus
service between New Delhi and Lahore, Pakistan began here Friday
morning in thick fog.
</P>
<P>
The bus implementing the dry run carried 19 officials from both
the central and Delhi governments including those from immigration
and customs departments, and security men.
</P>
<P>
G. S. Cheema, chairman of the Delhi Transport Corporation who
was among the first group of passengers on the bus, said before
departure that the officials would make an on-the-spot assessment
about halts and other necessary arrangements including security
and safety of the route.
</P>
<P>
Regular bus service along the 650-kilometre route between New
Delhi and Lahore would start after January 20, it was officially
announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It was officially arranged that the bus, which will take 14
hours on the way, would run four times a week from both sides.
</P>
<P>
The bus service is considered to be one of the major
understandings between the prime ministers of the two countries
for improving relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
