<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Calls for Greater Contributions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin,
general secretary of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central
Committee today called for scientists and technicians to make
greater contributions to the full-scale revitalization of the nat
ion.
</P>
<P>
Jiang issued the call during a meeting of winners of awards
for scientific and technological advances in 1998. The meeting
was held in the Great Hall of the People.
</P>
<P>
Mankind is witnessing a global scientific and technological
revolution, and the trend for continued economic and social
progress will rely mainly on knowledge. He said the importance of
creative applications of knowledge is becoming increasingly
apparent.
</P>
<P>
Scientific and technological advances are becoming an
important force in promoting progress of mankind, said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
"Any failure to closely follow the tidal wave of scientific
and technological advances will leave us in an extremely passive
situation," according to the president.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China must unswervingly implement Deng
Xiaoping's Theory that science and technology are primary
productive forces. He said the strategy for using science and
education to revitalize the nation and strategy for pursuing
sustainable growth must be carried out in a timely manner.
</P>
<P>
Jiang urged Chinese scientists and technicians to unite and
continuously accomplish new achievements in order to make new
contributions to the full-scale rejuvenation of the nation.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji and Vice Premier Li Lanqing also
attended the meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
