<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Cuts Interest Rates by 0.25 percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Association of
Banks Friday decided to cut the association's deposit rates by
0.25 percent to 4 percent across the board with effect from
January 11, the fifth interest rate cut since October last year.
</P>
<P>
The association made the announcement after its committee
meeting here Friday, saying the move was made in view of the
continuing lower trend of market cost of funds.
</P>
<P>
Starting from next Monday, the rate for both savings and 24
hours' Call/ Notice will be 4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's major banks, the Hongkong and Shanghai Banking
Corporation Ltd., Standard Chartered, Bank of China Hong Kong
Branch and Hang Seng Bank, also announced Friday to reduce their
prime lending rates by 0.25 percent to 8.75 percent from next
Monday. 
</P>
