<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Passenger Arrivals in Macao Rise Last November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Passenger arrivals in Macao by
means of marine, land and air routes were 556,005 in November
1998, an increase of 7.6 percent over the same month of 1997,
figures released Friday by the Macao Census and Statistics
Department show.
</P>
<P>
Passenger arrivals in Macao in November also rose slightly
from the 551,516 persons in October 1998.
</P>
<P>
However, the number of passengers to Macao from January to
November dropped 1.4 percent from a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
During the 11 months, passenger arrivals from China's mainland
areas and Hong Kong accounted for 75.8 percent of the total,
resulting in an increase of 6.9 percent over the same period of
the previous year.
</P>
<P>
But those from the Republic of Korea, Japan and Southeast
Asian countries plunged 76.2 percent, 44.6 percent and 35.7
percent, respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
