<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Enterprises Adopt Trade Rights Registration System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Over 6,000 large industrial
enterprises will simply have to complete registration procedure
to receive trade rights beginning this month.
</P>
<P>
 According to the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation (MOFTEC), the registered state-owned industrial
enterprises will be permitted to import and export their own
products.
</P>
<P>
 Enterprises administrated by the central government can
register directly with MOFTEC, while firms under the
administration of local governments will be required to submit
registration applications to foreign trade departments in their
respective provinces, autonomous regions, municipalities and
cities with provincial status.
</P>
<P>
 The move will surely sharpen the competitive edge of the
large enterprises and expand exports, the MOFTEC sources said.
</P>
<P>
 Statistics indicate that the 10,708 Chinese manufacturers
with trade rights account for 10 percent of China's total trade
volume.
</P>
<P>
 All large industrial enterprises have been granted the
import and export rights jointly by the State Economic and Trade
Commission, State Development Planning Commission, State
Statistics Bureau, Ministry of Finance, Ministry of Labor and
Ministry of Human Resources since 1992. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
