<HEADLINE> Cambodian Defense Minister Urges to Careful handle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, January 8 -- Cambodia's Co-Defense Minister Tea
Banh emphasized Friday that Khmer Rouge issue must be handled
carefully and skillfully, because it concerns the peace and
stability of the country.
</P>
<P>
Tea Banh told the reporters after the meeting of ministers of
cabinet that government's decision to allow the defectors to
return to Pailin, a western province controlled by defected Khmer
Rouge leader Ieng Sary, was a "special way for Cambodia to bring
peace and stability and end suffering for the country."
</P>
<P>
When asked about if there was a danger of renewed war, Tea Banh
said:" We can not say at the moment before the Khmer Rouge leaders
are arrested, but more fighting would bring suffering to Cambodia
again."
</P>
<P>
"It (the Khmer Rouge issue) is rather complicated and
particular. We should not focus on certain person but also on
others," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
So far, three Khmer Rouge leaders have surrendered to the
government. Ieng Sary surrendered in 1996. Khieu Samphan and Nuon
Chea surrendered to the royal government on December 25 and
received warm welcome from the government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
