<HEADLINE> China Publishes Yellow Book on World Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of Social
Science (CASS) today released the Yellow Book on the World
Economy -- Analysis and Prediction for 1998-1999 authored by
well-known Chinese economists in the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
The 300,000-character book, published by the China Social
Science Documentation Publishing House, discusses economic
situations in major countries and regions in 1998 and offers
predictions for economic development in 1999.
</P>
<P>
The work also covers major problems and pressing issues
concerning the international economy, including the "euro" and
the "knowledge-based economy".
</P>
<P>
Economist Wang Luolin, the executive CASS vice-president,
noted that China's economic development is becoming increasingly
tied to the global economy.
</P>
<P>
The work, which has both academic and practical significance,
will be published on an annual basis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
