<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong Customs Forms Anti-Smuggling Force </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The Customs Office in south
China's Guangdong Province announced the official formation of
police force today as part of its effort to strengthen the
anti-smuggling campaign.
</P>
<P>
The new force will operate directly under the customs and the
public security departments and will consist of eight branches at
major customs offices, including Guangzhou, Shenzhen, Gongbei,
Shantou and Huangpu.
</P>
<P>
The force will include 53 anti-smuggling units and special
investigative agencies in 40 customs offices throughout the
province, according to a recent announcement by General
Administration of Customs.
</P>
<P>
The anti-smuggling force will be staffed by 2,710 agents and
will be the largest unit of its kind in China.
</P>
<P>
The initial 556 agents and customs officers are currently on
duty.  
</P>
</TEXT>
