<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Addresses Military Modernization (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
said recently that the combat effectiveness of the People's
Liberation Army (PLA) has been upgraded to a new stage over the
past two decades.
</P>
<P>
He also noted that the PLA has made significant contributions
to safeguarding and building the country, as well as promoting
world peace.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin, chairman of the Central Military Commission, made
the comments during an important military conference held on
December 25, 1998.
</P>
<P>
"The principle of building a modern army with Chinese
characteristics ensures the army's preparedness for ward-off
preemptive strikes, as well as large-scale wars and nuclear war,"
according to Jiang.
</P>
<P>
"We have implemented a strategy of using science and
technology to strengthen the army, and are focusing on related
development rather than intensive manpower.
</P>
<P>
"The PLA has withstood serious tests and has strictly adhered
to a correct political orientation, while at the same time
maintaining the true nature and purpose of the people's army, as
well as a high degree of stability and concentrated unity."
</P>
<P>
"Facts prove that the Chinese army is indeed the people's army
under absolute leadership of the Communist Party of China. The
army is politically qualified, fully capable of passing the stiff
tests and completely reliable to work for the Party and the
people," said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
He specifically cited the counteroffensive in the late 1970s,
a series of joint military maneuvers between May 1995 and June
1996, the garrisoning of troops in the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR) on July 1, 1997, and the victory
over record summer flooding in 1998.
</P>
</TEXT>
