<DOCNO> XIE19990108.0101 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Addresses Military Modernization (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang said the highest priority in military modernization must
be placed on revolutionizing the army in order to determine the
nature and orientation of the PLA modernization.
</P>
<P>
The major contradiction facing the PLA is the incompatibility
between China's modernization level and the demand for modern
warfare, said Jiang. He added that the army must center on its
modernization drive in order to increase its combat readiness.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said the modernization drive demands regularizing the
army. He noted that an important task of the regularization
centers on defining the basic achievements and experience in
revolutionization and modernization in the form of laws and
regulations to ensure that the military operates in strict
accordance with the law.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that properly handling the relationship between
quantity and quality is vital to the military modernization
effort.
</P>
<P>
The worldwide development of science and technology, as well
as improvements of military hardware make "it increasingly
important to improve the quality of the PLA," said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
He said the key aspect for improving quality lies in using
science and technology to invigorate the army and to increase its
defense and combat effectiveness.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also pointed to army's dependence on people as its
source of strength.
</P>
<P>
"The strategic theory of a people's war requires a capable
standing army and powerful reserve forces to ensure national
defense," said Jiang, adding that China must maintain smaller
troops in the peacetime and mobilize more forces in times of war.
</P>
<P>
He said the formation of a reserve national defense force must
comply with the characteristics of future military operations and
the requirements for a socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
The president said concerned departments must work hard to
improve the quality of reserve forces, and both the
organizational system and relevant policies.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990108.0102 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Addresses Military Modernization (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"We have correctly grasped and solved several important issues
related to military modernization over the past 20 years," said
Jiang. "It is essential for us to seriously summarize past
experiences in order to further promote military modernization
and realize both national defense and military goals."
</P>
<P>
Jiang outlined several aspects related to the historical
development of military modernization. He pointed to the
relationship between war and peace, and noted that for a long
period in the past, China faced serious political and military
threats from the blockade and hostilities from the outside.
"Preparing for the danger of war was correct," said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
However, the international situation was subject to monumental
changes between 1980 and 1990. The CPC Central Committee affirmed
that easing international tensions represented an irreversible
trend. The committee also concluded that enjoying a good
international climate and good relations with neighboring
countries was indeed realistic.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, according to Jiang, China must unswervingly conduct
reform and opening, while continuing to accelerate the
modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
"Hegemonism and power politics still exist," said Jiang. "We
must resolutely safeguard the unity of the motherland and the na
tion's territorial integrity."
</P>
<P>
"We must carry out military modernization drive and be fully
prepared for the possibility of a military confrontation,"
according to the president.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also elaborated on the relationship between national
defense and economic construction. "Two strategic tasks for the
modernization drive center on energizing and ensuring a strong
national defense."
</P>
<P>
"The development of national defense must be subordinated to
economic construction. We must extend great efforts to strengthen
national defense while concentrating on economic construction,"
said Jiang, adding that "we must forge a system which ensures the
coordinated development of national defense and economic
construction."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990108.0103 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Addresses Military Modernization (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang noted that the long tradition of the PLA represents an
essential guarantee for maintaining the nature and combat
strength of the army.
</P>
<P>
The PLA has carried out a series of reforms over the past two
decades and has recorded significant breakthroughs in improving
both its modernization and combat effectiveness.
</P>
<P>
He instructed the army to deepen reform and formulate policies
and measures in line with the socialist market economy to enhance
the initiative of all sectors of the PLA.
</P>
<P>
The PLA's modernization drive must be conducted in line with
the tide of worldwide military innovation and development, said
Jiang, adding that the PLA must actively absorb the useful
experience of armies of other countries, especially developed
countries.
</P>
<P>
However, he stressed that "the PLA is a people's army under
the absolute leadership of the Chinese Communist Party and as
such must retain its unique political nature and advantages
instead of simply copying principles of foreign armies."
</P>
<P>
He said the PLA's achievements and experience in military
modernization over the past two decades proceeded under the
guidance of Deng Xiaoping's ideas on building the Chinese army in
the new era.
</P>
<P>
"We must continue to follow Deng Xiaoping Theory while
exploring the road ahead and must further enrich and develop the
late leader's ideas on military modernization," said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said the army must go all-out to train more outstanding
young officers who have both abilities and moral integrity to
ensure the energetic development of the People's Liberation
Army.  
</P>
</TEXT>
