<HEADLINE> Special Stamps to Be Issued in HK for Chinese L </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 8 (Xinhua) -- A set of special stamps on
the theme of "Lunar New Year Greetings" will be issued in Hong
Kong on January 31, P.C. Luk, acting postmaster general of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, announced here Friday.
</P>
<P>
This set of special stamps is to celebrate the traditional
Chinese Lunar New Year, Luk said.
</P>
<P>
For the first time, the stamps will be printed with a layering
of gold-colored "scratch off" ink, which, when removed, will
reveal an auspicious message suitable for this most important
Chinese festival, he added.
</P>
<P>
The four stamps in the set depict greetings associated with
customs of the Lunar New Year and there will be mini panes for
the four denominations each containing ten stamps with different
greeting messages. 
</P>
