<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNITA Forces Raid Diamond Mine, Killing Four </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The soldiers of the rebel National
Union for the Total independence of Angola (UNITA) Thursday raided a diamond
mine in Lunda-Norte Province, killing four people, including two
foreigners.
</P>
<P>
The Angola Diamond Company announced Friday that the deceased were
Patrick Bergin, a British and Mario Trepechio, a Brazilian and two Angolan
security men.
</P>
<P>
The mine under the diamond company was actually paralyzed after the
killing, which brought "extreme terror" among workers and some foreign
managers and technicians were planning to leave, said Chairman of the
management board of the company, jose Dias.
</P>
<P>
Diamond is the foreign currency-earner for the government and major
economic source for UNITA's purchase of weapons and logistics supply.
</P>
<P>
The Lunda-Norte Province is one of the important diamond production
areas in Angola, an area haunted by UNITA men. There were two
slaughters in the area in 1997, when 150 and 24 people were killed
respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
