<HEADLINE> Earthquake Safety Day to Be Observed in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, January 8 (Xinhua) -- An Earthquake Safety Day will
be observed in Nepal for the first time on January 16-18, the
official RSS news agency said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Programs to raise awareness will be organized at the
governmental, semi-governmental and non-governmental levels, RSS
said.
</P>
<P>
An exhibition will also be held on ways to protect oneself and
others from earthquakes, the news agency added.
</P>
<P>
Both local and international experts had predicted a big
earthquake in the near future in the Kathmandu Valley, which lies
in the seismic belt.
</P>
<P>
A tremor measuring 8.4 on the Richter scale rocked Nepal on
January 15, 1934, killing about 4,300 people.
</P>
<P>
Another earthquake measuring 6.4 on the Richter scale claimed
some 700 lives in 1989 in the Himalayan kingdom. 
</P>
</TEXT>
