<HEADLINE> 1 Killed, 3 Injured in Riots in Karawang, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- One student was killed, three
men
were injured and hundreds of shops, showrooms, department stores
and
four police stations damaged Friday as riots broke out in the
Pasar
Johar area in Karawang, West Java Province of Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
The official Antara News Agency said the riots erupted at 9:00
a.m.
when thousands of people began pelting the buildings with stones
after hearing a rumor that a driver of an Ojek (rented motorcycle)

got a traffic fine ticket and a kick from a policeman Thursday
night.
</P>
<P>
Until Friday afternoon, the riots were still raging and even
spread to other parts of the city, located some 60 kilometers east
of
Jakarta.
</P>
<P>
At least four cars were destroyed in the riots and one of them
was
burned by the rioters.
</P>
<P>
Karawang Police Chief Lt. Col. Achmad Hidayat said that
provocateurs could be behind the incident and that he had heard of
the riot plan three days ago.
</P>
<P>
The police have nabbed dozens of people participating in the
riots.
</P>
</TEXT>
