<HEADLINE> Malaysia Introduces Computer Competency Test </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia Friday launched a
PC competency test (PCCT) formulated to gauge one's ability and
efficiency in the application of information technology (IT).
</P>
<P>
The introduction of the PCCT which is internationally
recognized is seen as timely as Malaysia is expanding the use of
IT.
</P>
<P>
The test helps employers intending to recruit workers who are
skilled in using the computer as those who have passed the test
will be awarded certificates.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia's Information Technology Competency Standards Sdn Bhd
(ITC Standards) in collaboration with United Kingdom's NCC
Education Services Ltd. have designed the software application for
the test, which can provide an effective and accurate approach in
evaluating one's competency in using computer applications
frequently used whether at home, in the office or on campus.
</P>
<P>
ITC Standards will initially introduce seven modules -- Basic
Concept of IT, Word Processing, Spreadsheet, Managing Files,
Database, Presentation and Graphics and Information Network
Services which could be taken for the test.
</P>
<P>
Ten IT education and training centers have been chosen as
authorized test centers to facilitate the sitting for the test.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
