<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 8 (Xinhua) -- More than 30 Tamil rebels were
killed and a large number injured when the Sri Lankan Navy
attacked a fleet of boats carrying rebels and arms in the
country's Eastern Province in the early hours of Friday morning, a
navy spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the attack which commenced around 2:00 a.m.
Friday continued till 6:00 a.m. close to the Salpeyaru beach at
