<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-08 08:39 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cyprus Stock Market in 1998 Yields Return of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The year 1998 concluded with
very satisfactory returns for the Cyprus Stock Market, while
market prices fluctuated intensely, a weekly market review said
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The review, issued by the Cyprus Investment and Securities
Corportion Limited (CISCO), said the CICSO All-share index closed
at 453.9 points as at December 31, 1998, achieving a capital
appreciation of 16.6 percent for the year.
</P>
<P>
The total market return for 1998, after taking into
consideration the dividend yield for the same period of 4.8
percent is estimated at 21.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
This return ranks 6th in the market's 15-year history, with
the year 1995 being at the top of the list with a spectacular
total return of 58.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
The first three trading sessions of the new year saw the
market being set on a slow, but uninterrupted advance. The CISCO
Al-share index closed on January 7, 1999 at 457.3 points, an
advance of 3.4 points or 0.7 percent since the year-end.
</P>
<P>
The total volume of transactions for the year 1998 reached
347 million Cyprus pounds (694 million U.S. dollars), compared
to 170.8 million pounds (341.6 million dollars) in 1997 and
231.4 million pounds (462.8 million dollars) in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Banking titles were the most actively traded stocks during the
year (absorbing 44.5 percent of the total volume), followed by
the warrants (13.1 percent) and insurance titles (11.9 percent).
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
