<HEADLINE> British PM to Visit Kuwait Saturday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, January 8 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister
Tony Blair will arrive here Saturday for a one-day official
visit, during which he will meet with senior Kuwaiti officials
and visit British forces stationed here.
</P>
<P>
Upon his arrival, Blair will be accorded an official
reception at Kuwait International Airport led by Crown Prince
and Prime Minister Saad Al-Abdullah Al-Salem Al-Sabah, Kuwait
News Agency Friday cited an official statement as saying.
</P>
<P>
Blair will then proceed to Kuwait's Royal Palace where he
will first be received by Kuwaiti Emir Jaber Al-Ahmad Al-Jaber
Al-Sabah, before holding official talks with senior Kuwaiti
officials on various issues.
</P>
<P>
The British premier is scheduled to address some 500
British troops stationed at Ali Al-Salem air-base, 80 kilometers
north of Kuwait City.
</P>
<P>
Twelve British Royal Air Force Tornado fighter plans are also
stationed at the air-base. The Tornadoes flew 28 missions
against Iraqi targets over the four-day U.S.-British air strikes
in December. 
</P>
