<HEADLINE> Israeli Universities to Hook up to NASA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Israel's universities will be
linked by a special computer connection to the U.S. National
Aeronautics and Space Administration to get reliable digital data
about the Earth, The Jerusalem Post reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted Science Ministry officials as saying
that the information to be provided by the NASA can be used
for weather forecast and applying data on soil moisture and
plant life for agriculture and meteorology.
</P>
<P>
The line will cost the ministry 30,000 U.S. dollars and
each university 10,000 dollars a year, the report said. Israel
will be the 10th country to be hooked up to the NASA, it
added. 
