<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Passengers, Cargo transport of Vietnam Airlines Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Passengers and cargo transport of
Vietnam Airlines decreased sharply in 1998, Vietnam's English
daily The Saigon Times Daily reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam Airlines carried about 2.48 million passengers in 1998,
compared with the previous year's 2.593 million, the daily quoted
a report from the carrier's corporate affairs office as saying.
</P>
<P>
The 1998 figure includes 900,000 foreigners, 85,337 fewer than
the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Cargo transport was 40,300 tons, including 15,600 tons on
international routes, much lower than 1997's figure of 45,239
tons.
</P>
<P>
Dao Manh Nhuong, director of Vietnam Airlines, told the paper
earlier this week that management had not yet finalized the 1998
balance sheet, but the drop in passenger numbers and the
depreciation of the Vietnamese dong against the U.S. dollar meant
higher losses for last year compared with 1997's 36 billion
Vietnamese dong (around 3 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Last year saw Vietnam Airlines cut out many local and
international services and reduce the frequency of flights on
others. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
