<HEADLINE> 10 Tamil Rebels Killed in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 8 (Xinhua) -- At least 10 Tamil rebels were
killed Thursday by Sri Lankan government troops in separate
clashes in Northern province of the country, a military spokesman
said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Ink Dewage said that during daytime Thursday in the
northwest of Oddusudan, government troops operating forward of
defenses sniped at and killed four Tamil rebels.
</P>
<P>
Around 10:30 a.m. Thursday at Paranthan, troops conducted a
limited operation and confronted a group of rebels. The troops
confirmed that four rebels were also killed during the
confrontation, he said.
</P>
<P>
In another incident around 11:15 a.m. Thursday at Paranthan,
Dewage said, government troops operating forward defenses killed
two more rebels.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday morning, at the sea off Mullaitivu, a Sri Lankan
naval craft on offensive patrol detected a rebel vessel and
engaged it with heavy naval weapons, Dewage said. The navy
confirmed that the rebel craft was destroyed.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a war against the
government since 1983 for a separate state in the north and east
of the island country. 
</P>
