<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Prioritizes Equipment Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Speaking at an ongoing work conference here, Sun Changji,
deputy director of the State Administration of the
Machine-Building Industry, said that China currently imports
close to 40 percent of its equipment needed in spite of its
surplus machinery production capacity.
</P>
<P>
Sun said the administration will expand production of 25 types
of products, including farm equipment such as heavy-duty
tractors, combines and grain driers and various other products
for the basic industry and infrastructure sectors, such as
generating units, environmental protection equipment, industrial
control systems and meters, mining equipment and refining
installations.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the production of single-cylinder diesel engines,
small tractors, combines, forklift trucks and loaders will be
limited.
</P>
<P>
The administration's ambitious plan calls for the industry to
generate an output value of 1,500 billion yuan and export
products valued at 34 billion US dollars by the year 2000.
</P>
</TEXT>
