<HEADLINE> Compulsory Education System In Northern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, January 8 (Xinhua) -- China's Ministry of Education
and Ministry of Finance recently praised Shanxi Province in
northern China for implementing a compulsory education project in
poverty-stricken areas.
</P>
<P>
A provincial government official says that Shanxi spent 600
million yuan during the 1996-1998 period on the project in 35
state-designated poverty-stricken counties.
</P>
<P>
By the end of July, 1998, Shanxi had added 282 primary schools
with a total of 21,000 square meters of floor space, and had impro
ved facilities at 164 schools, and given training courses to
46,000 teachers.
</P>
<P>
Shanxi was able to do this because its plan for implementing
the compulsory education project has given priority to primary
schools, rural areas, and construction of schools.  
</P>
