<HEADLINE> Viagra Undergoing Clinical Trial in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 8 (Xinhua) -- China's drug administration
is conducting clinical experiment on Viagra, whose fate in China
will be decided later this year, when the results of the study
are released.
</P>
<P>
Seven hospitals in the cities of Beijing, Shanghai, and Wuhan
are trying it out on about 600 male volunteers, Guangzhou's
"Yangcheng Evening News" reports. It quotes a State Drug
Administration official as saying that the results will partly
decide whether Pfizer, the American manufacturer of Viagra, is
allowed to sell the little blue pill in China.
</P>
<P>
Strict clinical tests have to be done, but the government
department still has the final say, the newspaper says. The
volunteers are married males above the age of 22 who have shown
been sick for at least six months, it says, suggesting that the
illness was impotence. They have already been given the medicine
or a placebo and have recorded relevant data and personal
feelings every day for a two-month period.
</P>
<P>
Viagra still does not have an official Chinese name in China,
but the media and black marketers are using the word "weige", a
term coined in Hong Kong.  
</P>
</TEXT>
