<HEADLINE> Beijing's Vegetable Growers Looking At Overseas Markets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Farmers in Beijing have been
opening contacts with overseas vegetable markets in recent years,
looking for higher profits through export.
</P>
<P>
 Beijing exported 120,000 tons of vegetables in 1998, four
times the 1997 figure, and earned 50 million U.S. dollars from
them. They went not only to neighboring countries but also to
Britain, Germany and the United States.
</P>
<P>
 Local officials say that this growth came from an increase
in the variety and the speed of transport. Beijing has more than
20,000 farmers in suburban areas growing vegetables for export on
more than 13,000 hectares of land.
</P>
<P>
 The exports have also accelerated the process of
industrialization in rural areas and the growth of companies that
specialize in vegetable processing.  
</P>
