share to help relieve the financial and economic crises in Japan
and Asia, said a senior European Commission official Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Leon Brittan, vice-president of the commission, the executive
body of the 15-nation EU, told visiting Japanese International
Trade and Industry Minister Kaoru Yosano that the EU had done a
lot in absorbing Japan's exports to accelerate the economic
recovery in both Japan and Asia. (EU-Japan)
</P>
<P>
