<HEADLINE> Myanmar to Hand Down Deterrent Sentences on Drug Offenders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar Central Committee for
Drug Abuse Control (CCDAC) is deliberating deterrent sentences on
drug offenders as part of its measures to step up drug fight in
the country.
</P>
<P>
A coordination meeting of the work committees of the CCDAC,
held here Thursday, also covered drug education which is to be
carried out among students.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, a total of 5,540 persons were
apprehended in 1996 in 3,771 drug-related cases and death
sentences were passed on 20.
</P>
<P>
The statistics also show 5,361 people were punished in
connection with 3,864 similar cases in 1997, and the figures for
the first six months of 1998 were 2,300 people charged with the
offenses.
</P>
<P>
The Myanmar CCDAC was formed in 1975 with 12 working groups
supervising the country's drug control activities. 
