<HEADLINE> World No. 1 Samsonov Upset by China's Wang Liqin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 7 (Xinhua) -- World number one Vladimir
Samsonov has a shock exit at the ITTF Pro-Tour finals here on
Thursday when he lost to China's Asian champion Wang Liqin.
</P>
<P>
The Belarussian, also defending champion at the tournament,
lost 21-17, 21-4 and 21-8, sending Wang into the last eight.
</P>
<P>
Other Chinese men's singles players also sailed into the
quarterfinal, with Olympic champion Liu Guoliang beating France's
amien Eloi 16-21, 21-10, 21-17, 21-13, and Kong Linghui routing
France's world number ten Jean-Philippe Gatien 21-19, 21-17,
21-13.
</P>
<P>
