who beat 1991 world champion Jorgen Persson of Sweden 21-17,
21-17, 21-18.
</P>
<P>
Reigning world champion Jan-Ove Waldner rallied from one set do
wn to overcome Germany's Peter Franz 17-21, 21-16, 21-13, 21-14,
setting up the only all-European quarter-final in the men's
singles. He meets Belgium's Jean-Michel Saive.
</P>
<P>
In a cliffhanging clash, former European champion Saive came
back from two sets down and 12-15 in the fifth set to defeat
Austria's Werner Schlager 21-18, 21-19, 20-22, 18-21, 23-21.
</P>
<P>
As the bottom half of the draw was monopolized by Chinese,
Kong meets compatriot and world number nine Yan Sen while Ma Lin
faces Wang in the quarterfinal.
</P>
<P>
Yan beat France's Christophe Legout 21-18, 21-16, 17-21, 21-18
while Ma disposed of Greece's Kalinikos Kreanga 21-23, 21-7,
21-10, 21-13.
</P>
<P>
