<HEADLINE> Serbs Block Roads in Kosovo to Protest Murder </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Over a hundred Serb civilians
blocked roads to Kosovo's capital, Pristina, on Thursday to
protest the murder of a Serb coal mine guard, the official Tanjug
news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Nobojsa Denic, 36, was killed by ethnic Albanian gunmen on
Wednesday near the Belacevac mine, 20 kilometers south of
Pristina.
</P>
<P>
Angry protesters said they wanted urgent measures to be taken
to prevent Serbs being targets of the ethnic Albanians.
</P>
<P>
The Serbian Socialist Party issued a statement in Pristina
condemning the killing of Denic by the Kosovo Liberation Army and
demanding severe punishment for the murderer. It also called on
Serb civilians to maintain calm and not to take extreme action.
</P>
<P>
The Kosovo Liberation Army is fighting for the independence of
Kosovo, a Serbian province where an estimated 90 percent of the
population are ethnic Albanians. 
</P>
