<HEADLINE> Shandong Keen to Develop Tourism Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, January 8 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province is
to increase its financial support for the development of tourism
resources this year to make the industry a growth area of the
local economy.
</P>
<P>
Governments at all levels should include tourism in their plan
for economic and social progress, a provincial official said.
</P>
<P>
The development of large tourism projects will be supported
with start-up funds for basic construction, he said.
</P>
<P>
He added that qualified tourism enterprises will receive
priority treatment in the issue of corporate bonds and stocks,
adding that measures should also be taken to encourage overseas
investment in the development of tourism resources.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that Shandong received 55 million
domestic visitors and 600,000 overseas visitors last year, with
tourism earnings totaling 24.6 billion yuan, about 3.33 percent
of the provincial gross domestic product.
</P>
<P>
In another development, Yantai, a coastal city in Shandong,
was named as one of the best tourist cities at a recent national
conference on the travel industry. 
</P>
