<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Guizhou
Province has been speeding up the development of local
non-governmental scientific and technological businesses in
recent years, and they have become a strong force in economic
growth.
</P>
<P>
The number of the enterprises involved rose from 800 in 1995
to more than 1,000 in 1998, with employee numbers rising from
17,000 to more than 30,000, 45 percent of which are scientists
and technicians.
</P>
<P>
Revenues generated by these enterprises jumped from 600 m
illion yuan in 1995 to 1.2 billion yuan in 1998.
</P>
