<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Retail Sales of Consumer Goods up 11 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The volume of Shanghai's
retail sales of consumer goods totaled 147 billion yuan in 1998,
up 11 percent from the previous year, according to official
statistics.
</P>
<P>
After adjusting to the negative price indices, the actual
growth rate was as high as 16 percent.
</P>
<P>
An analysis shows that retail sales grew nearly eight percent
for state and collective commercial enterprises, 5-8 percent for
private and cooperative firms, and more than 15 percent for
shareholding enterprises and firms funded by investors from Hong
Kong, Macao and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Retail sales of consumer goods in the suburban markets rose
eight percent last year, about three percentage points lower than
the increase rate for the urban markets.
</P>
<P>
Experts note that supermarkets and convenience shops are
playing an increasingly important role in ensuring Shanghai's
commercial prosperity.
</P>
<P>
In another analysis, sales of aquatic products, meat and
edible oil grew by 30 to 55 percent last year, while sales of
electric cookers and computers jumped more than 50 percent and
those of air conditioners 25 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
