<HEADLINE> Shandong Produces 38.56 Tons of Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, January 7 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province
produced 38.56 tons of gold in 1998, the largest amount among all
Chinese provinces, according to official statistics.
</P>
<P>
Official figures also show that Shandong had the lowest gold
production cost per unit, with the processing cost standing at an
average 290 yuan per ton of gold ore, down from 324 yuan in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Shandong raked in 600 million yuan in profits from the gold
sector last year, about 60 percent of the national total.
</P>
<P>
A senior gold official in the province said that Shandong
plans to cut its per-ton processing cost to less than 280 yuan
this year, which is close to advanced world levels.
</P>
