<HEADLINE> Indonesia Looks Ahead to Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia is preparing squads
in eight sporting disciplines for the Sydney Olympics, an
official of the country's sports governing body KONI said here
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The eight squads, which include boxing, weightlifting, ya
chting, badminton, taekwondo, athletics, tennis and beach
volleyball, represent the country's hopes for a medal chase based
on their good records set at the last Asian Games in Bangkok.
</P>
<P>
"However, we can't confirm their inclusion in the team because
they still have to pass the qualifying events in order to go to
Sydney," said M. Hindarto, chief de mission of the Indonesian
contingent to Bangkok.
</P>
<P>
He called on the sports federations to prepare as early as
possible for the qualification series programmed by the
International Olympics Committee (IOC).
</P>
<P>
Some of the sports will have joined the qualification rounds
as early as March, he was quoted by the Indonesian Observer
Friday as saying.
</P>
<P>
M.F. Siregar, an official of the Indonesian Badminton
Federation, said that the federation had listed a number of
players including Ricky Subagja and Rexy Mainaky, gold medalists
at the Asian Games, mixed doubles pair Trikus Heryanto and
Minarti Timur, and Hendrawan and Taufik Hidayat.
</P>
<P>
Taufik is one of the Indonesian athletes who received
financial aid from IOC under the program of Olympics Solidarity.
</P>
<P>
Other Indonesian hopefuls are the mixed pairing of Zelin
Resiana and Bambang Supriyanto. Siregar jokingly appealed to Joko
Supriyanto to delay Zelin's pregnancy in order that his wife can
"do her duty".
</P>
<P>
Taekwondo, whose contribution at the Asian Games ended up in
silver medals, is currently preparing 24 nominees, who are
undergoing their training in three towns -- Batam, Yogyakarta and
Surabaya.
</P>
<P>
The athletes were between 16 to 24 years old, who are expected
to reach their peak at the Sydney Olympics, said general
secretary of Indonesian Taekwondo Association Zarkasih Hamid.
</P>
<P>
The weightlifting federation will nominate five weightlifters
for the four-yearly world multi-sport event.
</P>
<P>
"We remain hopeful for the Olympics particularly in women's
events," said Djoko Pramono, general secretary of the
weightlifting federation. 
</P>
