<HEADLINE> China's Light Industry Output Grows by 9.7 Percent in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 8 (Xinhua) -- China's light industry sector
realized a gross output value of some 1,250 billion yuan in 1998,
up 9.7 percent on an annual basis, according to the latest
statistics from the State Administration of Light Industry.
</P>
<P>
 The figures also indicated that pre-tax profits last year
hit approximately 36 billion yuan, on a par with 1997.
</P>
<P>
 Chen Shineng, director of the administration, said that
despite the negative impact of the Asian financial crisis, the
country's light industry sector still increased its exports by
over one percent from the previous year to reach 54 billion US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
 The light industry sector is now capable of making more than
300,000 kinds of products, with output value and export volume
accounting for one-third of the country's total. 
</P>
