<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kosir Leads after First Leg </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Slovenia's Jure Kosir edged out
1994 Olympic champion Austrian Thomas Stangassinger to lead after
the first leg of a World Cup slalom in Schladming, Austria on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Kosir clocked 47.29 seconds before a crowd of some 30,000
Austrian fans while the World Cup slalom leader Stangassinger
trailed the Slovene 0.06 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Italian Giorgio Rocca finished third in 47.48.
</P>
<P>
Fabrizio Tescari posted the equal fourth time of 47.84
together with Norwegian Hans-Petter Buraas.
</P>
<P>
Buraas, the reigning Olympic champion who had a disappointing
start this season, is eager to claim a first World Cup victory.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
