<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing to Improve Service for Border Entry and Exit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Beijing's border entry and exit
department has announced it will start processing passport and
visa applications every Saturday plus weekdays from January 9,
this year.
</P>
<P>
It has also pledged to increase efficiency during its daily
8-hour work schedule and strictly observe relevant laws and
regulations in handling applications, according to Yu Guohai, a
division chief of the department, which is part of the Beijing
Municipal Public Security Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Since China began its reform and opening-up in 1978, Beijing
has witnessed an increasing number of residents who travel
overseas, study or do business abroad.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that more than 100,000 Beijing residents went
overseas for unofficial business in 1998, while the city handled
applications from nearly 100,000 foreigners for border entry and
residence.  
</P>
</TEXT>
