<HEADLINE> Afghan Taliban Releases Another 264 POWs of Opposition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 7 (Xinhua) -- The Afghan Taliban are
reported to have released another 264 prisoners of war (POWs) of
the opposition under a decree of Taliban supreme leader Muhammad
Omar in respect of Eird-ul-Fitr, a major Muslim holiday which
comes after Ramadan.
</P>
<P>
According to a report Thursday by Radio Shariat, out of the 264
POWs, 200 were released from Pul-e-Charkhi Prison while the rest
were released from Kunduz Prison.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban have freed the opposition's prisoners of war
unilaterally and without any agreement, the report said. It was
the fourth time the Taliban authorities have released the POWs of
the opposition in respect of Eid-ul-Fitr.
</P>
<P>
The report said that intelligence officials of the Taliban
authorities visited the prisons and ordered the release of
prisoners on behalf of the Taliban supreme leader, Omar. 
</P>
