<HEADLINE> European Football Chief Threatens to Boycott World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 7 (Xinhua) -- European football governing body
UEFA president Lennart Johansson warned FIFA on Thursday that
Europe may not take part in the World Cup if they press on with
proposals for a biennial tournament.
</P>
<P>
According to local reports on the day, Johansson is furious
with FIFA president Sepp Blatter's plan to change the four-yearly
World Cup to two-yearly without consultation with Europe and
other continental federation.
</P>
<P>
Johansson said: "I was extremely surprised we went back to the
old system where the president makes statements about anything
without asking anyone."
</P>
<P>
FIFA will debate the plan this month. 
</P>
