<HEADLINE> UK Trying to Contact Six Britons Arrested in Yemen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 7 (Xinhua) -- The United Kingdom said on
Thursday that it was trying to make contact with six Britons who
have been detained in Yemen.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Office said it had been informed by the Yemeni
authorities earlier in the day that six Britons had been detained.
</P>
<P>
"As soon as we were informed, our consul-general sought the
earliest possible access to the men. This has yet to be granted
but efforts to see the men will be strongly maintained at the
highest levels," a spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Yemen's interior minister was on Wednesday quoted as saying
that an eight-man Western sabotage gang had been arrested in Aden.
He said seven of them carried British passports.
</P>
<P>
Three Britons and an Australian were killed last week when
Yemeni troops stormed the hide-out of kidnappers who had seized 16
western tourists.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday two British detectives probing the deaths were
told to leave Aden and were later allowed to go on with their
investigation.  
</P>
