<HEADLINE> UNSCOM Likely to Call Advisory Board Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, January 7 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Special Commission (UNSCOM) in charge of dismantling Iraq's
weapons of mass destruction may call a meeting of its advisory
board in New York shortly, U.N. spokesman Fred Eckhard said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The board, which is made up of arms experts and foreign
ministry officials from countries around the world, last met in
September.
</P>
